## interrupts

**Value type:** `<prop-encoded-array>` encoded as an arbitrary number of interrupt specifiers

The *interrupts* property of a device node defines the interrupt or interrupts that are generated by the device. The value of the *interrupts* property consists of an arbitrary number of interrupt specifiers. The format of an interrupt specifier is defined by the binding of the interrupt domain root — specifically the `#interrupt-cells` property of the interrupt controller.

*interrupts* is overridden by the *interrupts-extended* property and normally only one or the other should be used. If both are present, *interrupts-extended* takes precedence.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi — 3-cell GIC specifier */
uart7: serial@880000 {
    interrupts = <GIC_SPI 608 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
};

/* Open PIC — 2-cell specifier: number + level/sense */
device {
    interrupts = <0xA 8>;
};
```
